707761f-a.text:
Second Avenue, east side, north from 3rd Street. In the foreground a gypsy woman and child are approaching the camera.
June 25, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

707762f-a.text:
Second Avenue, east side, north from and including 60 Second Avenue between 3rd and 4th Streets. This part of Second Avenue is the
home of Yiddish musical comedy and drama.
June 25, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.

710867f-a.text:
45 East 3rd Street, adjoining the N.E. corner of Second Ave. Building shown is the Eastern Hospital.
June 25, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
